[6] Ecuador (Quito)
Date: Thu 6 Oct 2011
Source: El Comercio [in Spanish, trans. Mod.JT, edited]
http://www.elcomercio.com/sociedad/sarampion-nino-Quito-Baca_Ortiz_0_567543344.html



Health Minister, David Chiriboga, confirms that there is a positive
case of measles in the Baca Ortiz Hospital. The patient is a
10-year-old child, and apparently the infection was the result of a
visit from a relative living in Ambato.

Additionally, it has been learned that there are 2 suspected cases in
Quito, one in the north and another in the south of the city.

--
